title: Static Analysis

android.permission.INTERNET.description: Allows an application to create network sockets.

android.permission.RECEIVE_BOOT_COMPLETE.description: Allows an application to start itself as soon as the system has finished booting. This can make it take longer to start the phone and allow the application to slow down the overall phone by always running.

android.permission.READ_PHONE_STATE.description: Allows the application to access the phone features of the device. An application with this permission can determine the phone number and serial number of this phone, whether a call is active, the number that call is connected to and so on.

android.permission.ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE.description: Allows an application to view the status of all networks.

android.permission.ACCESS_WIFI_STATE.description: Allows an application to view the information about the status of Wi-Fi.

android.permission.FOREGROUND_SERVICE.description: Allows a regular application to use Service.startForeground

android.permission.WAKE_LOCK.description: Allows an application to prevent the phone from going to sleep.

android.permission.VIBRATE.description: Allows the application to control the vibrator.

android.permission.GET_TASKS.description: Allows application to retrieve information about currently and recently running tasks. May allow malicious applications to discover private information about other applications.

android.permission.PACKAGE_USAGE_STATS.description: Allows the modification of collected component usage statistics. Not for use by common applications.

com.google.android.c2dm.permission.RECEI.description: Permission for cloud to device messaging.

manifest_analysis.title:
Clear text traffic is Enabled For App
[android:usesCleartextTraffic=true]
manifest_analysis.desc: The app intends to use cleartext network traffic, such as cleartext HTTP, FTP stacks, DownloadManager, and MediaPlayer. The default value for apps that target API level 27 or lower is "true". Apps that target API level 28 or higher default to "false". The key reason for avoiding cleartext traffic is the lack of confidentiality, authenticity, and protections against tampering; a network attacker can eavesdrop on transmitted data and also modify it without being detected.
manifest_analysis.name: Clear text traffic is Enabled For App [android:usesCleartextTraffic=true]

nx.description: The shared object has NX bit set. This marks a memory page non-executable making attacker injected shellcode non-executable.

stack_canary.description: This shared object has a stack canary value added to the stack so that it will be overwritten by a stack buffer that overflows the return address. This allows detection of overflows by verifying the integrity of the canary before function return.

relocation_readonly.description: This shared object has full RELRO enabled. RELRO ensures that the GOT cannot be overwritten in vulnerable ELF binaries. In Full RELRO, the entire GOT (.got and .got.plt both) is marked as read-only.

rpath.description: The shared object does not have run-time search path or RPATH set.

runpath.description: The shared object does not have RUNPATH set.

fortify.description: The shared object does not have any fortified functions. Fortified functions provides buffer overflow checks against glibc's commons insecure functions like strcpy, gets etc. Use the compiler option -D_FORTIFY_SOURCE=2 to fortify functions.

Como muitas empresas, usamos serviços que ajudam a fornecer anúncios baseados nos interesses aos nossos usuários. A Lei de Privacidade ao Consumidor da Califórnia de 2018 (CCPA) classifica o uso desses serviços como uma “venda” de suas Informações Pessoais para as empresas que fornecem serviços. Isso porque permitimos que tais serviços coletem informações de nossos usuários (como por exemplo, identificadores on-line e atividade de navegação) para que eles possam ajudar a veicular anúncios mais propensos a lhe interessar. Sob o CCPA, a partir de 1º de janeiro de 2020, os residentes da Califórnia têm o direito de optar pela exclusão da venda de Informações Pessoais sobre eles ou sua família. No entanto, esses direitos não são absolutos e estão sujeitos a certas isenções. Em certos casos, podemos recusar o seu pedido conforme permitido por lei. Para obter mais informações sobre como coletamos, usamos e compartilhamos informações pessoais dos residentes da Califórnia na operação de nossos negócios, e os direitos dos residentes da Califórnia sob a CCPA em relação a Informação Pessoal, por favor, revise nossa Política de Privacidade.

Como exercer seus direitos de exclusão ou outros direitos de privacidade da Califórnia

"personal_information_details" : "Your Right to Opt Out of Sale of Your Personal Information

Like many companies, we use services that help deliver interest-based ads to our users. The California Consumer Privacy Act of 2018 (CCPA) classifies our use of these services as a “sale” of your Personal Information to the companies that provide the services. This is because we allow such services to collect information from our users (e.g., online identifiers and browsing activity) so they can help serve ads that are more likely to interest you.
Under the CCPA, beginning January 1, 2020, California residents have the right to opt out of the sale of Personal Information about them or their household. However, these rights are not absolute and are subject to certain exemptions. In certain cases, we may decline your request as permitted by law. For more information about how we collect, use and share Personal Information of California residents in operating our business, and California residents’ rights under the CCPA with respect to that Personal Information, please review our Privacy Policy

How to Exercise Your Opt-Out Rights or Other California Privacy Rights

There is no charge for making privacy-related requests.

If you would like to opt out of the sale of your personal information, if any, there are two ways you can proceed:

(1) you or your authorized agent or representative may email us at privacy@psafe.com or contact us via postal mail at the following address:

PSafe Tecnologia S.A.
Caixa Postal 10900
Avenida Nossa Senhora de Copacabana 540, Loja A
AC Copacabana
Copacabana, 22020-970
Rio De Janeiro, RJ, Brazil

Please note that we may need to confirm your identity or California residency to process your request. Note also that our applications collect certain data automatically and share it with advertising networks to customize the ads you see within the applications. If you submit an opt-out request, we will cease sharing the data that we have collected to date; however, If you do not uninstall the application(s) after submitting such a request, or if you reinstall the applications(s) in the future, the application(s) will share the data collected during future uses.

(2) You can submit an automatic opt-out request by activating the slider at the bottom of this page. In this case, we will cease sharing the data that we have collected to date; however, if you remove and then reinstall the application on your device, or if you install the application on a new device, the application may share data again until you submit another opt-out request per the procedures herein described.

There may be settings within your device that prevent applications from collecting and sharing this kind of data. To change these settings on your device, please follow the instructions for your device below.

How To Adjust Your Device And/Or Browser Advertising-Related Settings

In addition to contacting us, you may wish to adjust your mobile platform settings to avoid personal information being sent generally to advertisers (enabling the “Opt out of Ads Personalization” setting). An overview of the steps to adjust your advertising preferences can be found at https://www.networkadvertising.org/mobile-choice.

Your mobile web browser may also provide a “Do Not Track” browser setting. When you have enabled this setting in your browser, advertisers should not use mobile web browsing information from that browser to infer your interests or serve ads to that device that are targeting based on your inferred interests.

Please note that while opting out limits advertisers’ collection of information to serve you ads based on your inferred interests, it does not prevent you from receiving ads from third parties.

playstore_details.description:
dfndr vpn (pronounced “Defender”) secures and protects your online activities from hackers. What is a VPN? A VPN, or virtual private network, uses encryption to secure your internet connection.  Your secure VPN connection hides your IP address, allowing you to use the internet at home, work, or on public Wi-Fi without fear of hackers. Enjoy your VPN anywhere you have internet access.

 More than a simple VPN app, dfndr vpn for Android is packed with powerful features: 
✓ One-Touch Connection 
✓ Anti-Hacking Protection
✓ Virtual Locations 
✓ Anti-Phishing Protection

👆 Connect With One Touch 👆
Secure your connection with the touch of just one button.

🛡️Be Invisible to Hackers 🛡️
Keep your identity anonymous when you are connected to the internet. dfndr vpn protects you from intruders trying to access your information and activities using your mobile device, even on open Wi-Fi networks.

🌎 Change Your Virtual Location 🌎
Change your location to access restricted content with geographic restrictions outside of the U.S.

🛑 Block Malicious Sites 🛑
Get additional protection from malicious links that hackers use to attempt to steal passwords and other sensitive information. With Anti-Hacking enabled, you’ll be alerted to phishing-related activities in apps such as SMS, Facebook Messenger, WhatsApp, or Chrome without ever having to click on potentially malicious links. 

✨ Upgrade to Premium ✨
dfndr vpn is free to use, but you can also enjoy dfndr vpn with unlimited data transfer and zero ads starting at $3.99 / month.  

⚠️ Join our fight against deceptive advertising ⚠️
PSafe is committed to the online safety and security of our users. Unfortunately, some third parties are illegally using our name and logo to create misleading ad content, such as in the form of “scareware” falsely stating that your device is infected with a virus. PSafe unequivocally denounces these “scareware” tactics. If you receive a suspicious “virus alert” type ad, please take a screenshot of the ad, copy the full browser URL link of the ad or its redirect and email both to: support@psafe.com. We appreciate your support in fighting these malicious practices.

How to identify fake virus alert ads:
https://www.psafe.com/report-fake-virus-alerts
